# Arduino Temperature & Humidity Monitor (DHT11 + LCD)

A simple Arduino project that reads temperature and humidity from a DHT11 sensor and displays the values on a 16x2 LCD screen. The display updates every second and includes basic error handling if the sensor fails to read.

## Features
- Reads temperature (Fahrenheit) and humidity using a DHT11 sensor
- Displays values on a 16x2 LCD
- Updates every second
- Handles sensor read errors gracefully

## Hardware Used
- Arduino Uno (or compatible board)
- DHT11 temperature/humidity sensor
- 16x2 LCD (LiquidCrystal)
- Jumper wires
- Breadboard

## Wiring Overview
- LCD connected to pins 7, 8, 9, 10, 11, 12
- DHT11 data pin connected to digital pin 3
- 5V and GND to both LCD and DHT11

## How It Works
1. The Arduino initializes the LCD and DHT11 sensor.
2. Every second, it reads:
   - Humidity (%)
   - Temperature (Â°F)
3. The values are printed to the LCD.
4. If the sensor fails to read, an error message is displayed.

## Skills Demonstrated
- Arduino C++ programming
- Sensor integration (DHT11)
- LCD interfacing with LiquidCrystal library
- Real-time data display
- Basic error handling

## Future Improvements
- Add thermostat functionality (relay control)
- Add Celsius/Fahrenheit toggle
